An 11-year-old boy has been banned from lessons with his classmates after teachers said that his hair had been cut too short.

Callum Freeman fell foul of 'zero-tolerance' rules at St Benedict Voluntary Catholic Academy in Derby after getting a haircut with ultra-short, grade one sides.

His mother, Sam Tillson, claims her son has been told he cannot rejoin his peers until his hair grows back because his short back and sides breaches the school's dress code.

