St Benedict's headteacher Dr Chris Reynolds said Callum had not been isolated and that merely placed in an ‘opportunities room’, instead of his normal timetable.

'We have a zero-tolerance policy towards breaking school rules,' he said.

'This will result in pupils being placed in our opportunities room, which is not isolation, where there are several other pupils and a teacher.

'He has not been told that he cannot be in school and we would far sooner have Callum here.'

